author: Gareth Davies For Mailonline
title: Black crow circles an eagle and then lands on its HEAD | Daily Mail Online
text: Pluming hell! The amazing moment a black crow circles an eagle and then lands on its HEAD while trying to defend its nest The hilarious photographs were taken in Tamilnadu, India, of the crow repeatedly landing on the eagle's head Judging by the pictures, it is quite clear the bird of prey is not too pleased with its unwanted guest's antics Greaves Henriksen, a 52-year-old amateur photographer, took the snaps and said he couldn't stop himself He believes the crow was attempting to defend a nearby nest in the same tree as the eagle in Southern India Published: 09:14 GMT, 8 February 2017 | Updated: 09:14 GMT, 8 February 2017 37 shares
